    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="442"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Inclosed please find copy of telegram received at
                    the Department of Justice yesterday afternoon.</p>
                <p>Please furnish the United States district attorney at Wilmington, N. C., directly
                    or through this Department, with all the evidence at your command in support of
                    the proceedings which have been instituted, and oblige,</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0468" n="1202" xml:id="pg_1202"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 34.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss type="from">District Attorney Aycock</gloss> to the <gloss
                                type="to">Attorney-General</gloss>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington, N. C</hi>
                            </placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-20">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1895</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Have libeled steamer <hi rend="italic">Commodore</hi> and cargo, under
                        section <hi rend="italic">5283</hi>, and have had arrested for violation of
                        section 5286 John G. Dillon, master; George H. Martin, first officer; Frank
                        p. Grain, second officer; Manuel Hendio, cook; John B. Vanivie, chief
                        engineer; and Mark Reilley, assistant engineer. Can you furnish any evidence
                        in regard to the shipment of arms and ammunition or the connection of
                        Charles Raymond or any of above parties with same?</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">C. B. Aycock</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">United States Attorney.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
